summary: I remember scrolling through MySpace back in the day and hearing this song called Stay Beautiful by an artist named @taylorswift...
body:
I remember scrolling through MySpace back in the day and hearing this song called Stay Beautiful by an artist named @taylorswift - I listened to that song on the bus to and from school every day daydreaming about my crush at the time *cringe* but just relating to the lyrics and enjoying how it made me feel. From then I was hooked. I remember feeling so excited when Taylor released Fearless, it literally became the album to my final year of high school and I just adored everything about it and about her! Here was this romantic dreamer writing pieces of magic that I could associate to almost everything I was going through at the time. I felt like I had a friend in Taylor’s music and I felt so inspired and was full of admiration and hope. I say hope because adolescence is hard and high school wasn’t my favourite experience but having something as special as music and a person who is speaking openly about feeling on the outside and turning it into motivation to pursue their dreams was exactly what I needed. I got to see Taylor play at a venue in Melbourne that was called Billboard at the time..I think it’s 170 Russell now? I remember the line weaving around the corner through china town and looking at my black paint chipped nails and pushing my ‘emo’ fringe aside before hearing the girls in front start gasping as a car pulled up - it was like 10 seconds and Taylor waved and walked inside and I was having an internal freak out..the freaking out continued inside when Taylor was peeking out from the room above during the support act and waving at us..it was such a cool gig. I hadn’t really been to a country music artists gig before let alone a Taylor concert, so didn’t know what to expect - the vibe the entire show was just magic, so much good energy that night, from the very beginning she has always made the fans feel so special.

Every time I’ve had the opportunity to see her since makes me feel so many things, I feel so proud and emotional and ridiculously excited. Nobody puts on a show like Taylor. It’s literally something I look forward to with every album release, that knowing you get to share a room with other people who share the same love and the same admiration for a few hours and take away this really special moment in time to cherish - it’s just the best.

Taylor’s music has been part of my growth and my journey. I can put on any one of her songs and be instantly transported to a memory or a moment. I can’t imagine not having her there for my journey. The darkest moments have been made that little bit easier and the highs feel like they have their own special soundtrack that bring a whole element of joy when you play them.

I have so much respect and admiration for Taylor, I relate to her on so many levels and feel that the warmth and light and generosity she brings to her fans is a testament to who she is as an artist and a human being. I have learned so much about ownership, learning from mistakes and never being afraid to feel.

In ten days I will attend my 7th Taylor concert since 2009, my first for the Reputation Stadium tour when Tay hits Melbourne! To say I’m excited is an understatement - clearly. I am sharing this moment with my best friend - an equally devout Swiftie and we have been counting down since buying tickets when they were announced in December last year. I cannot wait to dance my ass off and hold on to the memories…(couldn’t help myself)..that will be made!
